WORKING WITH SCHOOLS, FAMILIES AND COMMUNITY ORGANIZATIONS, SELF ENHANCEMENT PROVIDES OPPORTUNITIES FOR PERSONAL AND ACADEMIC SUCCESS, BRINGING HOPE TO INDIVIDUAL YOUNG PEOPLE AND ENHANCING THE QUALITY OF COMMUNITY LIFE.
IRS990.Description: CORE PROGRAMMING:SELF ENHANCEMENT, INC. IS ONE OF THE NATION'S MOST COMPREHENSIVE AND SUCCESSFUL YOUTH DEVELOPMENT ORGANIZATIONS. 90% OF PROGRAM PARTICIPANTS OVERCOME SIGNIFICANT BARRIERS TO SUCCESS (POVERTY, FAMILY SUBSTANCE ABUSE, GANG INVOLVEMENT, ABSENT PARENTS, LOW ACADEMIC ACHIEVEMENT, ETC.) TO BECOME POSITIVE, CONTRIBUTING CITIZENS WHICH IS DEFINED AS AT LEAST 2 YEARS OF POST-SECONDARY EDUCATION OR EMPLOYMENT. CORE PROGRAM SERVICES ARE BASED ON THE RELATIONSHIP MODEL (TEACHER/PARENT/MENTOR); OFFERED IN A CULTURE OF SUCCESS; COMPREHENSIVE (SUMMER, IN-SCHOOL AND AFTER-SCHOOL); AND OFFERED ON A CONTINUUM (SERVING STUDENTS FROM AGE 8 THROUGH 25). EACH STUDENT IS ASSIGNED TO A COORDINATOR WHO MONITORS THE STUDENT'S ATTENDANCE, BEHAVIOR, AND ACADEMIC ACHIEVEMENTS. AN INDIVIDUAL SUCCESS PLAN IS CREATED FOR EACH STUDENT WHICH SETS ACADEMIC, PERSONAL, AND SOCIAL GOALS. ACADEMIC SUPPORT, ARTS EXPERIENCES, RECREATION ACTIVITIES, COMMUNITY SERVICE OPPORTUNITIES, LEADERSHIP TRAINING, AND SOCIAL AND LIFE SKILLS CLASSES ARE OFFERED THROUGH THE AFTER-SCHOOL PROGRAM. AN INTENSIVE 6-WEEK SUMMER PROGRAM KEEPS STUDENTS ENGAGED YEAR-ROUND. DURING THE 2009-2010 SCHOOL-YEAR SELF ENHANCEMENT SERVED 1,022 STUDENTS IN THE CORE PROGRAM AND 100% OF THE SENIOR CLASS GRADUATED FROM HIGH SCHOOL.

Activity2.Description: NON-CORE YOUTH PROGRAMMING:SELF ENHANCEMENT SERVES ANOTHER 2,000 YOUTH EACH YEAR THROUGH A VARIETY OF NON-CORE PROGRAMS. SELF ENHANCEMENT MANAGES 6 SUN COMMUNITY SCHOOLS PROGRAMS, PROVIDES SOCIAL AND SUPPORT SERVICES FOR EDUCATIONAL SUCCESS UNDER THE MULTNOMAH COUNTY SUN SERVICE SYSTEM FOR BOTH REGION 2 AND AFRICAN AMERICAN TARGET OUTREACH POPULATION.

Activity3.Description: COMMUNITY + FAMILY PROGRAMMING:SELF ENHANCEMENT RECOGNIZES THAT AT-RISK YOUTH MOST OFTEN COME FROM AT-RISK FAMILIES. THE POSITIVE WORK WE DO WITH YOUNG PEOPLE DURING THE DAY AND AFTER-SCHOOL CAN EASILY BE UNRAVELED BY AN UNHEALTHY SITUATION IN THE HOME. FOR THIS REASON, SELF ENHANCEMENT'S PROGRAMS INCLUDE OUTREACH SERVICES TO FAMILIES SUCH AS COUNSELING, CASE MANAGEMENT, PARENTING CLASSES, OR REFERRALS TO OUTSIDE RESOURCES. SELF ENHANCEMENT PROVIDES CULTURALLY COMPETENT SUPPORT SERVICES THROUGH THE FAMILY ENHANCEMENT PROGRAM, THE DOMESTIC AND SEXUAL VIOLENCE PREVENTION PROGRAM, THE COMMUNITIES OF COLOR MULTI-DISCIPLINARY TEAM, PLUS ASSISTANCE WITH BASIC NEEDS SUCH AS HOUSING AND ENERGY ASSISTANCE.

ActivityOther.Description: OTHER PROGRAMMING:OTHER PROGRAMS INCLUDE PROGRAM ADVANCEMENT AND REPLICATION. PROGRAM ADVANCEMENT FOCUSES ON INTERNAL TRAINING AND CODIFICATION OF THE SELF ENHANCEMENT, INC. PROGRAM MODEL. THE REPLICATION PROGRAM WAS ADDED IN 2007-2008 TO PROVIDE SUPPORT FOR THE EXPLORATION AND DEVELOPMENT OF A PLATFORM FOR REPLICATING THE SELF ENHANCEMENT, INC. PROGRAM MODEL IN OTHER CITIES.
